summary: Mature B Cells are Required for Acute Splenic Infection, but Not for Establishment of Latency, according to a new study. The study was conducted by the Watargion Unswrsty School of Medicine in Morocco. It looked at the role of B and CDS T cells during acute und cares 7HV-48 indection.
